A message of solidarity on the one year since George Floyd was murdered by officer Derek Chauvin of the Minneapolis Police Department, the same department where in 2006 officer Jason Anderson shot and killed 19 year-old Fong Lee.

The system protects white folks and allows officers to continuously commit murder and walk away with a mere slap on the wrist, meanwhile a family and a community is mourning and expected to carry on. No more. Solidarity is how we all get free. Solidarity is when we all mobilize together. Solidarity is how we unite. Today and every day we remember George Floyd and Fong Lee and everyone who the system wasn't built for and failed. We see them, and their family, friends and communities are always in our heart.

This video is one of 14 created by the May 19th Project, a newly formed collective promoting solidarity within Asian and Pacific Islander communities and with all communities, under the hashtag #SolidarityIs. They are working in collaboration with the Asian American Foundation (TAAF) and their #SeeUs campaign, a positive narrative against anti-Asian violence.

