White supremacy and its divisive tactics have made many of us see our struggles and oppression as separate for so long. All of our fights are intrinsically connected. Black and Asian solidarity has been rooted in us through our ancestors for decades, and today we celebrate Malcom X and Yuri Kochiyama, two activists who beautifully share the same birthday.

Listen to these never heard stories told by these two trailblazers grandchildren, and join the collective fight for liberation and freedom.

